===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms}}
{{och-l|畏|to fear}} is the exoactive derivation of {{och-l|威|to overawe}}, literally "to be intimidated" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). In early writing, the character for {{lang|zh|畏}} was sometimes used directly as a substitute of {{m-self|zh|威}} (e.g. in the {{w|Da Yu ding}} inscription).

{{och-l|鬼|ghost}} is a derivation ({{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 1998}}).

